headline: Tesla stock rises as US moves to ease rules for self-driving cybercab
summary: Investing.com -- Tesla (NASDAQ:TSLA) stock rose 2.6%, hitting a session high on Friday after a report that the US government is taking steps to ease regulations that have hindered the deployment of self-driving vehicles without driver controls.
